io.spine.server.storage

Class RecordStorageDelegate<I,R extends com.google.protobuf.Message>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.spine.server.storage.AbstractStorage<I,R>
      • io.spine.server.storage.RecordStorage<I,R>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - the type of the record identifiers
    R - the type of the message records
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Storage<I,R>, java.lang.AutoCloseable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    EntityRecordStorage, MessageStorage

    public abstract class RecordStorageDelegate<I,R extends com.google.protobuf.Message>
extends RecordStorage<I,R>
    A RecordStorage which delegates all of its operations to another instance of RecordStorage.

    The framework code deals with many objects that need to be stored. Some of them are the records of Entity states, some aren't (e.g. Events). The concrete storage implementations for these objects vary in API and functionality. However, neither of them performs the save/load operations themselves. Instead, they create a separate RecordStorage, configure it according to the properties of respective stored objects, and use it as a delegate. This type serves as a base for all such storages.

    Such an approach standardizes the way to store and query all objects in the system. It makes the creation of a new storage type as simple as extending this type and passing the RecordSpec corresponding to the stored object, into its super(..) constructor.

    In order to allow the descendants to configure the visibility of their API themselves, most of the methods of this type is made protected. The particular implementations are able to override these methods with the required level of visibility, if needed.
